<headline>Excessive Heat Warning issued June 27 at 1:45AM MDT until June 27 at 8:00PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque</headline>
<description>...EXCESSIVE HEAT WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 8 PM
MDT THIS EVENING...
* WHAT...Dangerously hot conditions with temperatures up to 112
degrees expected.
* WHERE...Chaves County Plains.
* WHEN...From Noon today to 8 PM MDT this evening.
* IMPACTS...Heat related illnesses increase significantly during
extreme heat events.</description>
<instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
